It’s tough to give skincare because it’s so personal. Here are the guidelines I tend to stick to;

🎁 a gift certificate for a facial is a great way to treat someone who may not usually treat themselves or hasn’t found the right match for their skin yet. You could help them find more than just a treatment, you can matchmake a relationship that can have continued impact. 

🎁 Body care is so much more likely to get used. Especially in the form of self care like a bath kit or body oil set. My top picks are the @oseamalibu Vagus nerve bath oil and pillow mist and @apoterraskincare luminous body collection. 

🎁 If you really have found success with a routine, teach your loved one how to do it. Practices like Gua Sha, dry brushing, facial masking etc. are all great for people looking to elevate their skin care. It doesn’t disrupt their regular products too much. I recommend stones from @mountlai and @treatmentbylanshin 

Hope this helps you as you wrap up your holiday shopping! I offer gift certificates for facials as well so just message me to connect. I look forward to caring for your loved ones. 

#therapeuticskincoach #burntoutbeauty #holidaygiftsets #skincaregift #skincareguide #dallasskincare

It’s been a wild ride, here are some highlights:

• Saw some friends and family
• Started offering facials again
• Got some help with health issues by addressing root causes 
• Traveled for work to places I’ve never been before

I’m not setting a resolution for 2023 but rather goals throughout the year. How was your 2022 and what are your goals for 2023?

Skincare resolutions you can actually keep 🙏🏻

💫 Clean makeup brushes help keep the skin happy. Especially if you’re prone to breakouts!
💫 Declutter so you can be intentional with your skincare usage. 
💫 Invest reusable items to help you commit to your daily skincare. 
💫 Be kind to yourself, your skin is listening! 

Just remember that small steps make a big impact y’all!

Happy new year 🎊

I also didn’t plan the chaotic white lotus theme to be perfectly times with the light flickering. 

These are daily habits I have added to my life to help heal my gut. These habits have been far more impactful to my life than a fad diet or restrictions. 

Just remember that digestion is a north to south process, it starts in the brain 🧠 the calmer and slower you move through a balanced meal, the greater chance you will digest well, absorb nutrients, and feel satiated. 

But of course, if any of these suggestions trigger disordered eating habits please seek support to help shape goals that are better suited for you. I’m a nutritional therapy practitioner that uses food as a source of healing for my gut and overall chronic illness. I have struggled with digestive issues and disordered eating as a result of it so I’m only sharing things that are a) science backed and b) tried and true by yours truly. 

Hope this finds you if you need the support!

Not my usual content but here’s where I share some growth. 

I don’t know why I ever took this comparison as an insult. I would be honored if anyone said this to me now. Especially since my appearance, something I once coveted, is in constant fluctuations. I’m puffy, bloated, swollen or sunken, dull, depleted by my chronic illness. I’ve learned to love myself in so many different variations of my appearance because under the exterior, I’m the same gal. The exterior doesn’t represent all of the essence of my soul. Which has taken a long time to accept, for fear that I would only be acceptable to others if I remained underweight and youthful looking. It’s cringe to type, let alone experience- but I know I’m not alone. 

The growth in what we view as beautiful starts with dismantling the internalized misogyny that has plagued many women of my generation. I see beauty in every type of person now unless they have a hateful heart. Not sure why I couldn’t see it back in 2009. 

I share this because as a person in the beauty industry, I feel a responsibility to break down the stupid standards set up to make people feel less than. Why? Because it blinds us to real beauty. 

And to @annehathaway - I see the beauty now more than ever. And I’m inspired by the kind heart most of all 💛

Sending love to those struggling with comparisons, unlearning impossible beauty standards, and who are just looking to love themselves. 

#therapeuticskincoach #burntoutbeauty #annehathaway #breakingbeautystandards #loveyourself💕

When I first started my career, I could barely get anyone to commit to exfoliating. It felt like a step people were nervous to take for fear that it would be too aggressive for their skin OR be an issue long-term. DING DING DING 🛎 Those concerns are so valid to me now because skincare has changed so much and our instinct is more = faster, better, deeper, etc. 

But that’s not how it works. Your skin is in a constant cycle of producing, maturing, and shedding. And with healthy circulation and a consistent routine of cleansing, hydrating, and protection, your skin will require far less exfoliating than you may think. 

A daily exfoliant (depending on the strength) can eventually start stripping at the barrier protection we need to have balance in the skin. Especially if you are not getting the results you’re looking for anyways. 

I opt for once a week for most cases which a mild exfoliant. Some people may benefit from more or less. And this consistency changes with age, stress, immune system, etc. 

I’m in no way anti-exfoliation, I think it’s necessary. Just the frequency and layering on exfoliating agents has to pair back overall. More is not better in this case. 

Hope this helps! 

#therapeuticskincoach #burntoutbeauty #skincareadvice #holisticesthetician #dallasskin

As one of my favorite teachers @wholisticskinandcare says; “No Flow, No Glow!”

You may be dealing with puffiness in the face, wrinkles on the neck, skin taking extra long to heal or bounce back from blemishes, and even tensions on the face as a result of neck neglect. 

This is so COMMON so don’t beat yourself up. And please don’t take anything out on your skin. There are many ways to get the neck back in flow. Connect with a holistic practitioner with experience in Gua Sha and/or manual lymphatic drainage to help as both those modalities are very neck focused.

Becoming an esthetician at 18 didn’t come with a manual on how to navigate peoples energy and how to build confidence in what I have to offer.

Going full time into facials again means that as a person with an inflammation disease, I have to prioritize my health and body with built in recovery days. 

I love @wesleywellness for having all the services I need to feel my best. 

First I started with a guided lymphatic roller massage for 30 minutes. This helps with circulation and stagnation while providing a nice full body massage. You start from the feet and work your way up! 

Next, 30 minutes in the infrared sauna for some meditation and sweat. People with endo have difficulty keeping their detox pathways working efficiently and sauna is one of the top recommendations to support liver health. 

Lastly, and I’m still working on the courage for this one, is a cold plunge for 3 minutes. The key here is breathing!! I eventually got my arms and hands in (which felt amazing since I’ve been doing tons of facials). I’ll get brave and dunk my head in soon 🫣

As someone with tons of clients and fellow estheticians who follow me on here, you have to know that we all need and deserve recovery. It’s not lazy to take a day off and it’s certainly worth the investment. I’ve not been great with making my health management a part of my schedule but embarking on a full time practice once again means I made this commitment to myself along with daily movement; dance, weights, functional movement, and/or walks outside! 

How do you recover?

Skin is tricky when we’re sick or stressed 😥 

However the most common instinct that my clients express is how they feel like they want to scrub off their skin when it’s flared from stress or sickness. 

My advice is to lean on hydration first. Hydrated skin will help your skin function better in so many ways:

- support the microbiome 
- reduce appearance of redness, fine lines, and texture 
- helps physically feel better from tightness and aches 
- will look dewy and glow

My 💦 solutions include:
- adding trace minerals to your water 
- increasing use of hydrosols and mist such as @linnebotanicals refresh, @apoterra neroli mist, @laurelskin hydrosols, and @joshrosebrook hydrating accelerator 
- mask with @co2lift 1x a week (that’s what I’m using for my client in this reel) 
- switch to oil cleansing until skin has calmed 

If you’re prone to congestion, don’t be scared - hydration will also help with that. 

Any questions? Sign up for my barrier restore facial for more!
